7. CMS Architecture
Data Model
Blog Post object (stored in localStorage['cms-blog-posts']):


{
  "title": "string",
  "slug": "kebab-case-string",
  "excerpt": "string",
  "category": "growth-frameworks|content-systems|philosophy|macroeconomics|productivity-systems|brand-strategy",
  "date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "readTime": "5 min read",
  "status": "draft|published",
  "content": "markdown string"
}
Playbook Post object (stored in localStorage['cms-playbook-posts']):


{
  "title": "string",
  "slug": "kebab-case-string",
  "excerpt": "string",
  "category": "content-system|growth|strategy|linkedin|branding",
  "date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
  "status": "draft|published",
  "content": "markdown string"
}
JSON Index entries (written to cms/blog-posts.json on publish):


{ "title": "...", "slug": "...", "excerpt": "...", "category": "...", "readTime": "...", "date": "..." }
localStorage Keys

cms-blog-posts        → JSON array of blog post objects
cms-playbook-posts    → JSON array of playbook post objects
gh-owner              → GitHub org/username (default: "ahmadfaroooq")
gh-repo               → GitHub repo name (default: "ahmadfarooq")
gh-branch             → Branch (default: "main")
gh-token              → GitHub PAT (never pre-seeded, entered by user)
GitHub API Integration
Class: GitHubCMS

Base URL: https://api.github.com/repos/{owner}/{repo}/contents
Auth: Authorization: token {PAT} header
getFile(path): GET file + SHA (returns null on 404)
putFile(path, content, message): GET existing SHA → PUT with base64 content
Encoding: btoa(unescape(encodeURIComponent(str))) — Unicode-safe base64

Seeded config (injected on first page open):


if (!localStorage.getItem('gh-owner')) {
  localStorage.setItem('gh-owner', 'ahmadfaroooq');
  localStorage.setItem('gh-repo', 'ahmadfarooq');
  localStorage.setItem('gh-branch', 'main');
}
Publish Flow
Validate: title, slug, GitHub config must exist
Open modal showing "Commit '{title}' to {owner}/{repo} ({branch})"
On confirm:
Save post to localStorage with status: 'published'
Generate HTML via buildBlogHTML(post) or buildPlaybookHTML(post)
Commit to blog/{slug}.html or playbook/{slug}.html
Filter all published posts → build index array
Commit cms/blog-posts.json or cms/playbook-posts.json
Show step progress (✓ HTML committed, ✓ JSON updated)
Close modal → Vercel auto-deploys in ~30s
HTML Generator Output Paths
Blog posts: blog/{slug}.html (relative paths use ../styles.css, ../scripts.js)
Playbook posts: playbook/{slug}.html (same ../ relative paths)
Generated HTML includes: full site header, nav, page-hero, prose section, footer
